text.tspan: Based on the expert assessments and index by the Economist Intelligence Unit (2023). It combines information on the
extent to which citizens can choose their political leaders in free and fair elections, enjoy civil liberties, prefer
democracy over other political systems, can and do participate in politics, and have a functioning government that acts
on their behalf. It ranges from 0 to 10 (most democratic).
